dc_title_s: The Literary Digest liberty map of the Western Front of the Great World War showing the battle line of liberty as it stood June 5th, 1918 : also showing the lines of farthest advance of the German and the French offensives with complete index
dc_description_s: Scale 1:506,880. 8 miles = 1 in.|Insets: Map of the complete war area showing Russian, Italian, Balkan, Palestine and Mesopotamian campaigns; also the zones of submarine blockade -- The coal and iron fields in the western war territory -- Production of pig iron in metric tons [and] coal in short tons.|OSU's copy 1 lacks index.|engraved and printed by the Matthews-Northrup Works, Buffalo, N.Y.
